990 IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, FINANCE COMMITTEE, EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE, AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR BEFORE FILING.

BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO SUBMIT WRITTEN CONFLICTS OF INTEREST TO THE BOARD PRIOR TO ELECTION TO THE BOARD, AND ARE REQUIRED TO SUBMIT TO THE BOARD ALL CHANGES AND ADDITIONS OF CONFLICT IN A TIMELY MANNER WHILE SERVING ON THE BOARD, AS STATED IN THE BOARD'S WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. ANNUAL DISCLOSURES ARE NOT REQUIRED; IT IS A SELF-POLICING POLICY.

COMPENSATION IS SET BY INDEPENDENT BOARD MEMBERS AFTER FORMAL WRITTEN REVIEW OF EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR BY OFFICERS AND SELECTED INDEPENDENT DIRECTORS. COMPENSATION IS BASED ON SALARY RANGES DEVELOPED BY PERSONNEL CONSULTANT.
